<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="951" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/11</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Minister of Guatemala</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 65</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your notes dated February 21, and 24, 1917, in which you
                            state that you have received information from the Government of
                            Guatemala to the effect that Guatemalan territory has been invaded by an
                            armed force from Honduras.</p>
                        <p>In reply I desire to inform you that this matter has been called to the
                            attention of the diplomatic representative of the United States in
                            Honduras, with the request that he report in full in regard to the
                            situation.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>